  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nIn the sdk `estimateL1Gas` and `estimateL1GasCost`, the nonce is converted to a number using toNumber without checking if it is defined. \r\n\r\nsee [estimateL1Gas](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/7b89c07212f906b210c52ecda97534e5ad968b46/packages/sdk/src/l2-provider.ts#L60) and [estimateL1GasCost](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/7b89c07212f906b210c52ecda97534e5ad968b46/packages/sdk/src/l2-provider.ts#L84)\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to the sdk\r\n2. call estimateL1Gas or estimateL1GasCost with a TransactionRequest object with nonce undefined\r\n3. See error\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nIf I am not mistaken, functions should estimate gas without requiring nonce since the nonce is automatically populated with etherjs\r\n\r\n**System Specs:**\r\n - Package Version (or commit hash): 1.1.4\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\ncan take care of opening a PR \r\n",
